def: Containing larval tapeworms; -- said of pork and beef.
To exchange anew; to reverse (a previous exchange).
Out of one's senses; distracted; mad. [Obs.] Shak.
Made of boxwood; pertaining to, or resembling, the box (Buxus).[R.]The faded hue of sapless boxen leaves. Dryden.
An artificial alkaloid of complex composition, resemblingthalline and used as an antipyretic, -- whence its name.
A perivisceral cavity which arises as an outgrowth oroutgrowths from the digestive tract; distinguished from aschizocoele, which arises by a splitting of the mesoblast of theembryo.
